{
  "number": 1934,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1934",
  "title": "Not able to unselect item in MultiRange",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nMaybe both? May not be something considered before now or something that was missed out in testing.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nWhen an item in a `<MultiRange />` is selected it cannot be unselected by clicking the same item again.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nWhen I click on an already selected item in a `<MultiRange />`\r\nThen that item should unselect and no longer be filtering results based on it\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nFrom what I can tell this is not something which is browser based\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nTo be able to unselect an active Range without having to select another range\r\n\r\nThis issue can be seen on the [React Storybook](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/storybook/?selectedKind=MultiRange&selectedStory=default&full=0&down=1&left=1&panelRight=1&downPanel=kadirahq%2Fstorybook-addon-knobs) for the MultiRange component.\r\n\r\nYou can select one of the items (such as <$10) but then cannot unselect it.\r\n\r\nWhile this could be unselected using the `<CurrentRefinements />` widget, I believe it's better suited to also have it available in the `<MultiRange />` component also.\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n2.2.5",
